  "analysis": "The current /app/mystery.c is an incorrect guessed raytracer and is verified wrong: image md5 a36bc6586fa014f9e174053d77d88f53 vs required e866fa2c851f4a9da736b4ed3ba3912e. The required behavior is known: print fixed messages and write image.ppm byte-for-byte identical to /tmp/original.ppm. We have /tmp/main_dis.txt and helper function addresses, but previous attempts to dump helpers/main chunks were truncated and no implementation has matched. The next concrete step is to dump the helper functions and main inner loop in small, non-truncated chunks to derive the exact algorithm.",
  "plan": "Dump vector_normalize and sphere_intersect first because they are essential for camera/ray and intersection logic, in small chunks (<=80 lines). Then dump main lines 81-160 separately. This will provide exact formulas for camera basis, ray generation, and sphere intersection needed for a correct implementation.",
